The first clash in the new local league run by the Louis Trichardt Cricket ClubÂ will take place next Saturday (17th) when Limpopo Dairy will test their strength against Vikings. A day later, on Sunday, Vikings will play against Strikers. The three teams competing in the local league will play against each other on a round-robin basis, with teams playing against each other twice. The final is scheduled for 15 April. The new league is a 20-over league, with teams comprising 11 players. The matches start at 14:00. Anyone interested in joining the Louis Trichardt Cricket Club can contact the club secretary, Naomi Phillipson, at 082-4847622.